Here is a rough step-by-step outline to set up AWX and Ansible using Docker. 
This was setup in a Ubuntu virtual machine environment.

STEP ONE: VIRTUAL MACHINE: 
-Linux 5.0.0-13-generic Ubuntu-19.04-desktop-amd64.iso
  -http://releases.ubuntu.com/19.04/
-Settings
  -3 CPU cores 
  -8 GB ram 
  -30 GB HDD 
  
STEP TWO: IN TERMINAL:
1. sudo apt-get update -y
2. sudo apt-get dist-upgrade -y
3. sudo apt-get install ansible -y
4. sudo apt-get install git -y
5. sudo git clone https://github.com/ansible/awx.git 
6. sudo apt-get install docker
7. sudo apt-get install docker-compose
8. cd awx/installer
9. sudo vim inventory
10. change top line to: localhost ansible_connection=local ansible_python_interpreter="/usr/bin/env python3.7"
11. 'esc' and then ':wq' to save and quit
12. sudo apt-get update -y
13. sudo apt-get dist-upgrade -y
14. sudo ansible-playbook -i inventory install.yml

STEP THREE: IN BROWSER:
1. visit http://localhost
2. USER: admin PW: password
